24/11/2003
NEW YORK, United States -- New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg arrives in Kosovo on Monday (24 November).
His office announced that he would be demonstrating "his support for the burgeoning democracy there", and would "bring greetings from the greater Albanian-American community in New York".
Bloomberg is scheduled to meet President Ibrahim Rugova, Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi and Pristina Mayor Ismet Beqiri.
He would also visit the US Camp Bondsteel base and meet with retired New York City police officers serving with the international police force in Kosovo.
(AFP - 21/11/03)
